1. Introduction
    This package is used for prepare Thecus kernel. It includes source files 
for Thecus device drivers, header, and the script for patching.

2. Installation
    Using the setup script to patch these source files to your specific 
Linux kernel source automatically.

3. Usage
   # cd thecus_drv_iscsi/
   # sh setup.sh <path of Linux kernel source>

NOTE:
* To prepare a full Thecus kernel source, your kernel source still needs to 
patch MD drivers which are not included in this package.

